  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering generally refers to the process of making illegally obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex transactions or legitimate businesses. Legal definitions can vary by jurisdiction, but typically involve three key stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source of funds through multiple transactions\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the funds into the economy as seemingly legitimate income\n\nMost legal definitions require:\n- Intentional concealment of the origin of criminal proceeds\n- Attempting to make illegal funds appear legal\n- Knowingly engaging in financial transactions with illegal funds\n\nSpecific details and penalties vary by country and jurisdiction.",
